VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)(?:password|passwd|secret|apikey|api_key|token|accesskey)\s*=\s*["'][A-Za-z0-9@#$%^&*!_\-]{8,}["']
WHEN EXPR MISSING:SecureString|Get-Secret|Vault|\$env:
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects hardcoded credentials or secrets assigned as plaintext string variables.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Hardcoded Credential in PowerShell Script.
